# Backend API — NestJS + TypeORM + Zod

## 0) Princípios de camadas
```
Controller  → valida HTTP, chama use-case, mapeia erro para HTTP
Use-case    → orquestra fluxo, regra de negócio (sem Nest, sem TypeORM)
Repository  → acesso a dados (TypeORM), queries por intenção
Domain      → entidades puras, invariantes, interfaces de repositório
```
**Nunca:** use-case com `HttpException` | controller com regra de negócio | entity TypeORM retornada direto na API.

---

## 1) DTOs com Zod (nestjs-zod)
```ts
// packages/shared/src/dto/create-lead.dto.ts
import { z } from 'zod'
import { createZodDto } from 'nestjs-zod'

export const CreateLeadSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, 'Nome obrigatório').max(120),
  email: z.string().email('Email inválido'),
  phone: z.string().regex(/^\d{10,11}$/, 'Telefone inválido').optional(),
})

export class CreateLeadDto extends createZodDto(CreateLeadSchema) {}
export type CreateLeadInput = z.infer<typeof CreateLeadSchema>
```

**Setup global (main.ts):**
```ts
import { ZodValidationPipe } from 'nestjs-zod'
app.useGlobalPipes(new ZodValidationPipe())
```

**Feature DTOs estendem PaginationSchema:**
```ts
// apps/api/src/common/dto/pagination.dto.ts
export const PaginationSchema = z.object({
  page: z.coerce.number().int().min(1).default(1),
  limit: z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100).default(20),
  order: z.enum(['ASC', 'DESC']).default('DESC'),
})
export class PaginationDto extends createZodDto(PaginationSchema) {}

// Feature:
export const FilterLeadsSchema = PaginationSchema.extend({
  search: z.string().optional(),
  status: z.enum(['active', 'converted', 'archived']).optional(),
})
export class FilterLeadsDto extends createZodDto(FilterLeadsSchema) {}
export type FilterLeadsInput = z.infer<typeof FilterLeadsSchema>
```

